  <mads:note type="nonpublic">Not to be confused with: Favorinus, fl. 104 B.C.?; another possible Favorinus, follower of Aristotle,
    mentioned by Plutarch; or Varinus Phavorinus (or Favorinus) Camera, i.e. Varinus (Guarino) of Favere near Camerino, Bp. of Nuceria, d. 1537</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">OCD, 2nd ed. (Favorinus; rhetor; born at Arles (Arelate) perhaps at beginning of Domitian's
    reign; teacher of Herodes Atticus, Gellius, and Fronto; wrote speeches, two miscellanies, sententiae; titles of nearly 30 works are known; 
    probably spoke and wrote Greek by preference; d. around the middle of the second century)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Dict. of Greek and Roman biography and mythology, 1967: v. 2, p. 139 (Favorinus; b. Arles; philosopher
    and sophist during Hadrian's reign) p. 139 (another Favorinus; Latin orator; mentioned by Gellius) p. 140 (another Favorinus, follower of Aristotle)</mads:note>
